@NODE intro "Introduction"
@{u}Introduction@{uu}

   This program allows you to create configuration files for KewlCDPro (by me),
ie. those .kewlcdpro files that KewlCDPro needs to know how to access a CD. In
the past there was AmiScanner, I didn't write it and it was a little bit buggy,
it also only created config files for Aminet CDs.

DirScanner can create config files for:

o  Aminet 1-5
o  Aminet 6+
o  Shareware Studio
o  CDs without index files (* - see below)
o  Unknown CDs

* - CDs without index files, you may think, "so why bother if they don't have
    any index files?" Well, the obvious solution is to make the index files!
    That's right, DirScanner will scan the CD and create index files as well
    as the config file (index files will be stored on hard disk).
    
Note: If you have any other types of CD, please send me how they are laid out
(e.g. where index files are stored and the directory structure).

   DirScanner also comes with a directory listing file, which will fill in
known directory descriptions for you! It also has a very nice gadtools GUI!
Aminet CDs have directory descriptions on the CD, but some descriptions are
too long - a shortened version of the description can be put in the main
directory listing file.

@ENDNODE


