@NODE install "Installation"
@{u}Installation@{uu}

   Copy the @{b}DirScanner.listing@{ub} file to @{b}S:@{ub} or keep it in the progdir, then put
the executable where you like!

   The @{b}LSD_Doors.key@{ub} or @{b}LSD_Otherreg.key@{ub} must be present in @{b}Sys:S/@{ub} for
DirScanner to work, which means you must be a registered LSD DOORS or Other-reg
user. It will open @{b}BBS:MAXsBBS.config@{ub} to confirm your keyfile, so you must also
have MAX's BBS installed. Seeing as KewlCDPro only works on MAX's BBS systems,
this shouldn't be a problem.

@ENDNODE


@NODE use "In use"
@{u}In use@{uu}

   Once you have @{" installed " LINK install} the prog, its time to check it out,
when you first run it you will see a window open with some buttons and stuff,
all the functions can be controlled by the keyboard, they are underlined.

@{b}The GUI@{ub}

@{u}T@{uu}ype of CD - Cycle gadget, lets you set what type of CD you are using.

@{u}S@{uu}can Dir - String gadget, enter the device and directory of the starting point
           to scan, any directories after this point will the scanned, most CDs
           have all their directories and files held beyond a directory.

@{u}V@{uu} - Pops up a file requester for the string gadget.

@{u}R@{uu}emove icons, etc - This tries to filter out icons, readmes and other
                    information that might be in a listing.

@{u}I@{uu}gnore empty dirs - This checks to see if directories are empty or possibly
                    problematic and filters them from the list. This function
                    slows DirScanner down a bit.

@{u}B@{uu}egin - Begin the file scanning.

@{u}A@{uu}bout - Shows some information.

@{u}Q@{uu}uit - Quits DirScanner (same as close gadget).

[ Information bar with status stuff in it ]

The string gadget automaticly checks and gets the proper device and directory
name, ie. if you enter @{b}cd0:aminet@{ub} on Aminet 18 it would become 
@{b}AMINET18:Aminet/@{ub}. It will tell you if the path doesn't exist. Heck, even if
you have Aminet selected you can just enter @{b}cd0:@{ub} and it'll come out
@{b}AMINET18:Aminet/@{ub}!

Once you are done, select Begin, if the path doesn't exist it won't let you
continue, if it does, then it will start doing its stuff, if you have selected
Unknown CD or CD without index files, a requester may appear if several
sub-directories were found asking you if you only the sub-most directories
(the lowest point) or if you want to use all directories.

If for example, the scan directory was @{b}Weird:Files/@{ub}, with all directories you
might have something looking like:

Weird:Files/Mad
Weird:Files/Mad/A-L
Weird:Files/Mad/M-Z
Weird:Files/Dodgy
Weird:Files/Dodgy/Odd

If you select only the sub-most directories you will get:

Weird:Files/Mad/A-L
Weird:Files/Mad/M-Z
Weird:Files/Dodgy/Odd

So pick which one suits the CD, if it doesn't (say its missed some important
files), then try the other, you can always re-create the config at any time.

Once it has finished it will save the file to @{b}Doors:KewlCDPro/CDConfigs/@{ub}
with a filename of @{b}<diskname>.kewlcdpro@{ub} where <diskname> is the disk name!

It will try to fill in as much information as possible in the config but check
it afterwards, you may have to fill in things like the section name, and
positions (see the KewlCDPro docs for more information).

If you wish to add any of your own directory descriptions, make a new file,
write them in, @{b}send them to me@{ub} and then append them to @{i}your @{ui}
@{b}DirScanner.listing@{ub} (either in @{b}S:@{ub} or @{b}PROGDIR:@{ub}, @{b}S:@{ub} is probably better).

Long directory descriptions will be truncated and little dotty things (..) will
be added to the end.

@{u}Note for Aminet CDs@{uu}

The @{b}info/adt/tree@{ub} file is used to read directory descriptions in, but
some descriptions are too long! So you may enter replacement descriptions into
the @{b}DirScanner.listing@{ub} as DirScanner will check this file first and then the
tree file.

After it has finished you will only be able to click ABOUT or QUIT, sorry :o).

@ENDNODE


